annotationA: Ecdysone oxidase; Choline dehydrogenase activity; flavin adenine dinucleotide binding; ecdysone oxidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: ecdysone metabolic process; oxidation-reduction process
annotationB: Shadow (Sad) is a cytochrome P450 involved in ecdysteroid biosynthesis. It shows a mitochondrial localization and catalyzes the addition of a hydroxyl group to the 2 carbon of the cholesterol ring. Sad mutants fail to undergo head involution, dorsal closure or to secrete cuticle
